Postman Endpoints for Trip Management

Base URL (local):

http://localhost:8080/api/trips

1️⃣ Create a new Trip

POST /api/trips

📌 Request Body (JSON):

{
  "destination": "Goa",
  "startDate": "2025-10-01",
  "endDate": "2025-10-07",
  "price": 15000,
  "status": "PLANNED"
}


📌 Response (201 Created):

{
  "id": 1,
  "destination": "Goa",
  "startDate": "2025-10-01",
  "endDate": "2025-10-07",
  "price": 15000,
  "status": "PLANNED"
}

2️⃣ Get all Trips (with pagination & filtering)

GET /api/trips?page=0&size=5&status=PLANNED

📌 Response (200 OK):

{
  "content": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "destination": "Goa",
      "startDate": "2025-10-01",
      "endDate": "2025-10-07",
      "price": 15000,
      "status": "PLANNED"
    }
  ],
  "pageable": {
    "pageNumber": 0,
    "pageSize": 5
  },
  "totalElements": 1,
  "totalPages": 1,
  "last": true
}

3️⃣ Get a Trip by ID

GET /api/trips/1

📌 Response (200 OK):

{
  "id": 1,
  "destination": "Goa",
  "startDate": "2025-10-01",
  "endDate": "2025-10-07",
  "price": 15000,
  "status": "PLANNED"
}


📌 If ID not found → (404 Not Found):

{
  "error": "Trip not found with ID: 99"
}

4️⃣ Update a Trip

PUT /api/trips/1

📌 Request Body (JSON):

{
  "destination": "Manali",
  "startDate": "2025-11-10",
  "endDate": "2025-11-20",
  "price": 20000,
  "status": "CONFIRMED"
}


📌 Response (200 OK):

{
  "id": 1,
  "destination": "Manali",
  "startDate": "2025-11-10",
  "endDate": "2025-11-20",
  "price": 20000,
  "status": "CONFIRMED"
}

5️⃣ Delete a Trip

DELETE /api/trips/1

📌 Response (204 No Content):

(no body)


📌 If ID not found → (404 Not Found):

{
  "error": "Trip not found with ID: 1"
}
